The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Management guru passes away
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Management guru passes away
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          C.K. Prahalad                                  
	Calcutta, April 17: Management guru C.K. Prahalad breathed his last in the US today after a brief illness.        
	He was 69 and is survived by his wife, a son and a daughter.        
	Coimbatore Krishnarao Prahalad is best known for the bottom-of-pyramid theory illustrated in his book The Fortune at the Bottom of the Pyramid: Eradicating Poverty Through Profit.        
	He was closely associated with many top companies such as Hindustan Unilever, business associations like the CII and educational institutions such as IIM-A.        
	Born to a brahmin family in the textile city of Coimbatore in Tamil Nadu, Prahalad did his graduation in science from the Loyola College in Chennai and his MBA from the Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad.        
	He wrote a doctoral thesis on multinational management graduating with a DBA degree in 1975 from Harvard Business School.        
	He then returned to India for a brief period where he taught at his alma mater  the Indian Institute of Management, Ahmedabad. He returned to the US to take up the position of the Paul and Ruth McCracken Distinguished University Professor of Corporate Strategy at the Stephen M. Ross School of Business at the University of Michigan.        
	He was honoured with Padma Bhushan in 2009 for his contribution in the fields of literature and education.        
	We have lost an outstanding management guru, CII director-general Chandrajit Banerjee said.        
	HUL chairman Harish Manwani said, CK was an invaluable member of the HUL board for the past 10 years and a great friend of the company.                                                                                                                                       
